To add the custom DSDT table you can use the script '01_acpi'.The script is 
written for ubuntu. We minor modification it can be used for any Linux distro.

1) Copy the DSDT.aml file to /boot/DSDT.aml

2) Copy the script '01_acpi' to /etc/grub.d

3) Do 'chmod +x' to '01_acpi' file.

4) Update GRUB config using (i.e., in ubuntu run 'update-grub2')

